      "text": [
        " : \"أَيُّمَا رَجُلٍ أَتَى رَجُلاً فَاسْتَقْرَضَ مِنْهُ مَالاً وَ فِي نِيَّتِهِ أَلاَّ يُؤَدِّيَهُ فَذَلِكَ اَللِّصُّ اَلْعَادِي\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3689 - Abu Khadijah narrated from Abu Abdillah (as) who said: \"Any man who goes to another man and borrows money from him while intending not to repay it, then he is a thief and a transgressor.\""
        ]
